13/04/2003
ISTANBUL, Turkey -- Turkey and Croatia have very similar defence objectives, according to Croatian Defence Minister Zeljka Antunovic, who spoke after a meeting in Istanbul on Friday (11 April) with the chairmen of Turkey's Parliamentary committees on foreign policy and internal affairs, Mehmet Dugler and Cengiz Kapetanoglou. Antunovic says the common defence objectives are establishment and protection of peace, security and stability in the two countries, as well as in Europe as a whole. He also met with his Turkish counterpart Vecdi Gonul, who pledged support for Croatia's aspirations to join NATO. (HINA, Anadolu Agency - 11/04/03)
